<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police say 11-year-old is serial burglar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) - An alleged 11-year-old burglar admitted to five
Brooklyn break-ins over the past five weeks, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The 4-foot-9 boy allegedly netted a collection of green cards,
ATM cards, jewelry and petty cash from the crime spree in the
Flatbush section, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The boy, who was not identified because of his age, was arrested
late Thursday when police spotted him climbing a fire escape,
apparently looking for an open window.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the tiny thief broke in to an apartment on Aug. 26,
and the following night stole some jewelry from a second home. On
Aug. 29, he allegedly grabbed a purse from another apartment, and
stole jewelry from a fourth apartment two days later.
</P>
<P>
   The last burglary happened on Sept. 1, when he stole documents
from a fifth apartment.
</P>
<P>
   The case was referred to Family Court and the boy was released
into his parents' custody.
</P>
</TEXT>
