<DOCNO> APW20000909.0074 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 14:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> With BC-NY--Forced Ritalin, Bjt and BC-NY--Kyle's Story, Bjt  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Facts about Ritalin
<TEXT>
<P>
   Drug: Ritalin is the brand name for methylphenidate.
</P>
<P>
   Manufacturer: Novartis, based in East Hanover, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Pharmacology: Ritalin and similar stimulant medications
(Dexedrine, Cylert, and Adderall) are used to increase brain
activity and reduce the symptoms of Attention Deficit Hyperactivity
Disorder. It is widely used to treat Attention Deficit Disorder.
</P>
<P>
   Side effects: nervousness and insomnia are the most common
adverse reactions. Other reactions include nausea, dizziness, loss
of appetite and anorexia.
</P>
<P>
   Other: Novartis states that the drug should not be used in
children under age 6, although studies show doctors are prescribing
the drug for preschoolers at an increased rate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-09-09-00 1413 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000909.0075 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-09 14:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> RETRANSMITTING  </HEADLINE>
