<HEADLINE> Juliette Lewis Wants To Be a Mom  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Juliette Lewis, who plays a surrogate mom in her
new movie ''The Way of the Gun,'' wants to be a real-life mom some
day.
</P>
<P>
   Just not quite yet.
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm very inclined toward motherhood,'' Lewis, 27, said in
Saturday's editions of The New York Post. ''And in the last year
particularly, I think about it on a monthly basis. It's a really
wild feeling. I love children.''
</P>
<P>
   Lewis has two new movies in the offing and says she wants to
''build up a nest egg'' before starting a family with husband Steve
Berra, a championship skateboarder who she wed a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Lewis has appeared in 30 movies, including ''Natural Born
Killers,'' ''National Lampoon's Christmas Vacation,'' and ''Cape
Fear,'' for which she won an Oscar nomination.
