<HEADLINE> 'Spinal Tap' Star Targets Dog Shows  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Christopher Guest's satirical films have taken
on rock 'n' roll, the film industry and small-town theater.
</P>
<P>
   His latest target? Dog shows.
</P>
<P>
   Guest, co-writer and co-star of ''This Is Spinal Tap,'' said he
had never been to a dog show before he made ''Best in Show,''
scheduled for release Sept. 29. In preparation for it, he went to
Westminster last year.
</P>
<P>
   ''It is intense,'' Guest told Time Out New York in its Sept.
7-14 issue. ''When some dogs came out, it could have been Prince
coming onstage.''
</P>
<P>
   Guest, who is married to actress Jamie Lee Curtis, said the
common thread in all his movies has been ''a fanaticism that
crosses different boundaries in hobbies or professions.''
</P>
<P>
   A re-release of ''This Is Spinal Tap'' opened in theaters
Friday.
</P>
