By The Associated Press	   A warm day with high temperatures near 80 degrees is
forecast
for Sunday. A chance of showers or a thunderstorm later in the day
is expected statewide.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sunday night should be humid in many areas with a low
temperature around 60 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   Monday looks to be partly or mostly cloudy with some scattered
showers or thunderstorms in eastern New York. The high temperature
will be in the 70s, according to forecasters. Western and central
New York can expect a mix of clouds and sun with a chance of
showers or thunderstorms. The high may reach the 70s.
