<HEADLINE> Wizards 2, Mutiny 2, Tie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay's Eric Quill scored two goals as
the Mutiny and Kansas City Wizards played to a 2-2 tie Saturday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay's Mamadou Diallo was held without a goal and finished
the regular season with a league leading 26. Diallo was robbed
twice from point-blank range by goalkeeper Tony Meola.
</P>
<P>
   Diallo was one short of Roy Lassiter's MLS record of 27 set in
1996.
</P>
<P>
   Chris Henderson and Miklos Molnar, who tied it in the 66th
minute, scored for the Wizards. Kansas City had beaten Tampa Bay
four straight times.
</P>
<P>
   Quill, who departed late in the second half with a right ankle
injury, put the Mutiny ahead 1-0 in the 8th minute. He redirected a
pass from Diallo from near the right post. Quill's second of the
game, and fifth this season came, on a give-and-go with Carlos
Valderrama in the 33rd minute.
</P>
<P>
   The assist extended Valderrama's MLS-record single-season total
to 26.
</P>
<P>
   The Wizards played without three injured starters: Preki (right
hamstring strain), Mo Johnston (right knee strain) and Chris Klein
(left hamstring strain).
</P>
</TEXT>
