<HEADLINE> 45 dead sea turtles wash up on New Jersey beaches  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BRIGANTINE, N.J. (AP) - The numder of dead sea turtles that have
washed up here, in Sea Isle City and the Holgate section of Long
Beach Island has reached 45 this year, according to the Marine
Mammal Stranding Center.
</P>
<P>
   That number, which includes turtles found Friday in those areas,
is about average for the season, according to Alexa Bracht, field
stranding technician at the center.
</P>
<P>
   In 1999, a total of 78 dead turtles were handled by the center.
</P>
<P>
   Bracht told The Press of Atlantic City for Saturday's editions
that the dead turtles weren't necessarily killed by boats, adding
that even those whose bodies are damaged by watercraft may have
died and floated to the surface before being struck.
</P>
</TEXT>
