<HEADLINE> Capello Sets Track Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Rinaldo Capello set a new track qualifying
record Saturday, winning the pole for Sunday's American Le Mans
Series Rose City Grand Prix at Portland International Raceway.
</P>
<P>
   Capello, driving an Audi R8 Prototype, raced around the
1.944-mile road circuit at an average speed of 108.820 mph,
breaking the record of 108.692 mph, set by J.J. Lehto last year.
</P>
<P>
   Capello will co-drive with Allan McNish in the two-hour,
45-minute sports car endurance event.
</P>
<P>
   The powerful Audi team is seeking its fourth consecutive series
win. The teams' other car is co-driven by Emanuele Pirro and Frank
Biel.
</P>
</TEXT>
