<HEADLINE> Fire 3, Crew 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Mike Sorber scored in the 90th minute
Saturday night, giving Chicago a 3-2 win over the Columbus Crew
after the Fire blew a two-goal lead.
</P>
<P>
   An unguarded Sorber got a pass from Dema Kovalenko about 10
yards out on the left side and sneaked a left-footer past Crew
goalkeeper Mark Dougherty, who got his right hand on the ball but
couldn't make the save.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago (17-9-6, 57 points) took a 1-0 lead on Peter Nowak's
goal in the 23rd minute and made it 2-0 on Ante Razov's 18th goal
three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Duhaney's goal in the 34th minute made it 2-1, and Columbus
tied the score on Brian McBride's goal in the 88th minute.
</P>
<P>
   Columbus lost out on the final Major League Soccer playoff spot
when Colorado beat Los Angeles on Friday. The Crew finished the
season at 11-16-5 for 38 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
