<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Reservist Killed, 1 Hurt in Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WAYNESBURG, Pa. (AP) -- An Army reservist fixing a tarp on a
military jeep was killed in a hit-and-run crash Saturday and
another was injured, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   Their Army convoy was traveling near the West Virginia border
when two of the vehicles pulled to the side of Interstate 79 so
reservists could fix a tarp that had come loose, state police said.
</P>
<P>
   A passing truck hit Donald Burge, 35 of Moundsville, W. Va., and
Joseph Howdyshell, 42, of Parkersburg, W. Va., police said. Burge
was thrown onto the roadway, where he was hit by a car and killed,
police said. Neither the truck nor the car stopped, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Howdyshell was listed in fair condition Saturday night at West
Virginia University Hospital in Morgantown.
</P>
</TEXT>
